Chilean Stocks: CTI and Sigdo Koppers Advance; Colbun Falls

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-08-22T20:07:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-22/chilean-stocks-cti-and-sigdo-koppers-advance-colbun-falls.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:16 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index rose fell 0.4 percent to 4,112.89.  CTI Cia Tecno Industrial SA (CTI)   jumped 11.7 percent to
a record 39.1 pesos. Sweden’s Electrolux AB agreed to pay $690
million to Chilean holding company Sigdo Koppers for CTI, its
Chilean home appliances unit.  Sigdo Koppers SA (SK)   rose 2 percent to 815.99 pesos.  Colbun SA (COLBUN)   fell 2 percent to 116.6 pesos.
Chile’s third-largest power generator posted a net loss of $16.1
million in the second quarter, compared with a profit of $55.5
million a year earlier, according to a filing sent to regulators
Aug. 19.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
